{
  "stem": "26142.13",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she, I, I escorted her the next day to the train station.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And she went, she went back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He regained consciousness.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and he lived about a few weeks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think-- I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had it marked down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Should have it on the day in March.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'll look it up a little later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one, that one day, my brother Tsvi and I-- we were smokers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, we didn't smoke inside.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We went out, we went out in the yard to have a smoke.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, and then a few minutes later, my mother came out to the yard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And said, she said, children, children, she said-- you know, in Yiddish, she said, you can cry.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You had a good father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that, and that was, and that was the end of-- the we started to cry and run inside.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We saw him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was, [? it was fine. ?] He was in great pain, in great pain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "On one way, in one way, I think he was, he was lucky.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He [? mattered ?] to know that his children were safe, more or less safe, and alive, and that we all were there, where he was buried in Debrecen.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "On the other hand, the, my mother was-- well, we'll talk about my mother later.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I don't know when she died.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "At least I went back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I went back from Allentown to, to Debrecen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And it's, it's, my brother, Eliezer, and his family were rounded up in 1944, in April.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And on, in March, he died in 1943 in March.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "In the [? matseyve, ?] you know, the tombstone, usually is put up eleven months later to the year.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
